metatags.og:title: Trump's Border Claims - FactCheck.org
metatags.og:description:
After a group of migrants tried to breach the U.S. border at Tijuana,
                   Customs and Border Protection Commissioner Kevin McAleenan said there were no "reported serious injuries on either side of the border." But President Donald Trump told reporters the same day that "three Border Patrol people yesterday were very badly hurt through getting hit with rocks and stones."

metatags.og:description:
In response to a question about climate change,
                   President Donald Trump falsely claimed that the United States was “the cleanest we’ve ever been.” Data from a variety of sources show that while the country has made strides in the last decade,

The president’s comments came on Nov. 26 after he was asked by a journalist about the latest National Climate Assessment.
